postcontent:
Note: I only have 2 available at this price.
The P-11 is a semi-automatic, locked-breech, DAO, pistol, chambered for the 9mm Luger cartridge. Ten round and optional twelve round magazines available. The Kel- Tec P-11 is compact and lightweight, thanks to its locked breech. Its ergonometry, perceived recoil and practical accuracy are comparable to much larger guns. The P-11 is especially well suited for plain-clothes police officers, security personnel, or as a secondary weapon for military service members.
The P-11 has six main component groups: barrel, slide, frame, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 Ordnance steel heat treated to 47 HRC. The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor. The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer and operates in Double Action Only. The hammer is driven by a novel free floating extension spring. The light weight firing pin transmits the energy of the hammer to ignite the primer. The functioning of the mechanism surpasses all applicable SAAMI safety standards. The grip is made of the ultra high impact polymer DuPont ST-8018. The grip also forms the magazine well and the trigger guard. Normally supplied with a 10-round double column all steel magazine.

title: For Sale:  Colt Officer's Model Target .22
postcontent:
The Officer's Model Target is Colt's top end pre-war target revolver. It was available in various calibers from .22LR to 32. to the .38 Special. These guns were built on the Colt "E" frame, which is the same as the Official Police "41" frame. This model made Colt's reputation as "THE" target revolver. In the 20's to the 40's many, if not most target shooter's used the Colt.The Officer's Model had a hand fitted and finished action, checkered trigger and backstrap, with an adjustable rear sight, and an adjustable front sight.Since the Officer's Model was Colt's premium target revolver,
the gun received extensive polishing and tuning of the action, for the best trigger possible.The pre-war Officer's Model had a great reputation, and are some of the finest fitted and finished revolvers ever made. Colt was using their famous heat bluing process in those days and the guns are gorgeous. No craftsmanship of this nature will ever be duplicated again.
DOB 1937
Caliber .22
Condition: used(if you didn't buy it from the factory or a dealer it is used) no box or papers. firearm appears to be unfired and in pristine condition. Every time I look at this revolver I think....I should shoot it and keep it. Or better yet let my wife shoot it and then I would be blameless in the decision.

title: For Sale:  Surplus Army M19A1 7.62X51mm NATO M80 (.30 cal) Ammo Cans
postcontent: These are surplus ammo cans straight from the White Sands Missile Range here in New Mexico.Â  From the designation on the can, you can see that these cans originally contained standard M80 ball cartridges in M13 linked belts.Â  The can would have contained two 100-round belts in cartons inside of the can. Model M19A1 Dimensions: 10â³ x 6.5â³ x 3.5â³ Steel ammunition chest Rubber seal Lay flat carrying handle Hinged lid Latch closure (can be locked with additional parts) These cans are in very good condition and the seals on them are in excellent condition.Â  The ammo in these cans would have been recently shot such that the cans are still in near mint condition. These can be used for ammo storage or any other items you wish to store in an air, humidity, and water-tight manner. You can depend on the can and seal to last many years. The cans are available for sale at our store in Rio Rancho and for those on the south end of town, in Belen. They are reasonably priced at $10.00 each, tax included.Â  We can also quote shipping costs based on how many you want and where they will be shipped to. These cans are generally known as .30 cal cans as they were originally designed to hold belts of .30 caliber machine gun bullets. The 7.62X51mm NATO round was developed in the 1950s for the M14 rifle and the M60 machine gun.Â  Since these cartridges were on linked belts that means they were intended for machine gun use, not rifle use.Â  Very few of these are used in rifles any longer as the M14 rifle was superseded by the M16 which used the 5.56X45 NATO round.Â  However the 7.62mm round known in the civilian world as the .308 Winchester is still used in sniper rifles and for other special purposes in addition to machine gun use. It was discovered in Vietnam that the M14 rifle was too long and heavy for jungle warfare and the size and weight of the cartridges limited the number of rounds that could be carried.Â  The commies had the same issue with their AK-47 ammo but they never wised up and still carry the bigger, heavier cartridges.Â  This chart helps show the comparison in what a soldier could carry:    Rifle Cartridge Cartridge weight Weight of loaded magazine 10Â kg (22#) ammo load   M14 7.62Ã51mm 393 grains (25.5Â g) 20 rds @ 0.68Â kg 14 mags / 280 rds   M16 5.56Ã45mm 183 grains (11.9Â g) 20 rds @ 0.3Â kg 33 mags / 660 rds   AK-47 7.62Ã39mm 281 grains (18.2Â g) 30 rds @ 1.2Â kg* 8 mags / 240 rds    (*AK-47 magazines are much heavier than M14 and M16 magazines) The 7.62X51mm cartridge remained the main machine gun round well in to the 1990s but for light machine gun use, has been replaced by the 5.56X45 NATO round in widespread use of the M249 SAW.Â  The 7.62 is still used in the M60E4, the M240 and by the Germans in their HK21 and MG3.We have also just gotten in some 40mm cans at our Belen location on sale for $25 each.*********************************************************************

Please only respond 1) if you are serious hunter and want to be part of something fun and 2)if you can afford this. I am not carrying any payment plan.

10 members will be $1000 each. If we decide to go with less hunters, the price goes up accordingly. I am paying full price as well.
Still hunt only, Georgia State rules for now. Plenty of Deer, hogs are starting to show up and a few bear are on the property. Small game and fishing.
Only charging enough to cover lease. Once established, we can decide on food plots, club stands (or not) etc. It will be family friendly. This should go quickly, so dont put off making the contact.
This is really a nice piece of land and will take very little effort to hunt it as is. Any modifications (food plots, club stands etc) would be easy and only add to the quality of the hunting experience. 
If you are interested, please contact me by email and we can set up a time for viewing. I am retired so any day of the week is good for me.
Please only respond 1) if you are serious hunter and want to be part of something fun and 2)if you can afford this. I am not carrying any payment plan.
